I&#x27;m sorry, I&#x27;m literally terrified of the people coming out of your organization after watching the video at the end of your post. I really question your organization&#x27;s judgement in evaluating developer talent if you&#x27;re seriously suggesting things like this (literally from your video):<p>- &quot;Googling for solutions is key&quot;  
- &quot;Marketers are the best at research&quot;  
- &quot;#2 is copying cool things&quot;...&quot;this is a key philosophy for you to understand how to use other people&#x27;s code&quot;<p>Ah yes, because that&#x27;s exactly how professional software engineering works. I don&#x27;t disagree that what people build is an effective way to judge them, but I question your organization&#x27;s ability to effectively judge a project through the lens of professional software engineering.
